deregisterForVAT.title = Deregister for VAT
deregisterForVAT.p1 = You can deregister from VAT if the business no longer needs to submit VAT Returns. We will review your reasons for deregistering within 3 weeks.
deregisterForVAT.p2 = If the business needs to deregister from any other taxes or schemes, you must do this separately.

deregistrationReason.title = Why is the business deregistering from VAT?
deregistrationReason.reason.stoppedTrading = It has stopped trading
deregistrationReason.reason.turnoverBelowThreshold = Annual turnover is below £83,000
deregistrationReason.reason.other = Other

deregistrationDate.title = Does the business want to choose its own deregistration date?
deregistrationDate.p1 = The deregistration date can be up to a maximum of 3 months from the date you submit your request.
deregistrationDate.p2 = We will confirm the deregistration date when your deregistration request is accepted.

deregistrationProperty.title = Does the business have any commercial property?
deregistrationProperty.p1 = This includes both land and buildings.

vatAccounts.title = How are the business’s VAT accounts prepared?
vatAccounts.accountant = If you have an accountant, ask them what accounting method they use.
vatAccounts.method.standard = Standard accounting
vatAccounts.method.cash = Cash accounting
vatAccounts.description.standard = You record VAT whenever you send or receive an invoice
vatAccounts.description.cash = You record VAT whenever you make or receive a payment

ceasedTrading.title = The date your business ceased or will cease trading
ceasedTrading.hint = For example, 31 3 1980

optionTax.title = Did the business charge VAT on land or commercial property?
optionTax.text = You can choose to charge VAT on any income earned from renting or selling land or commercial property. This is known as ‘Option to Tax’.
optionTax.hint = What was the total value of what the business charged?
optionTax.hidden.text = Although land and commercial property is usually exempt from VAT, some businesses choose to charge VAT so they can recover costs from construction or repairs.

capitalAssets.title = Does the business have any capital assets to sell?
capitalAssets.text.1 = This includes things like buildings, land, furniture, computers and other raw material or equipment.
capitalAssets.text.2 = Do not include intangible assets, for example patents, copyrights or goodwill.
capitalAssets.totalSaleValue = What is the total value of what you are planning to sell?

cannotDeregister.title = The business cannot deregister from VAT
cannotDeregister.text = This is because the business expects its taxable turnover for the next 12 months to be above £83,000.
